  bool-string-converter.hbs — static helper emitted into the helpers output
  directory (default: `Helpers/`) whenever a model property uses
  `@encode(string)` on a boolean (supported since TypeSpec 1.14.0).

  Provides `BooleanStringJsonConverter`, a `System.Text.Json` converter that
  serializes a `bool` as the JSON string `"true"` / `"false"` and reads it back
  case-insensitively (also tolerating native JSON `true` / `false`).

  Properties encoded this way are annotated with
    [JsonConverter(typeof(<HelpersNamespace>.BooleanStringJsonConverter))]
  so this helper must be present in the same compilation unit.  The converter
  targets `bool`; System.Text.Json applies it to `bool?` properties too.

  Override via tspconfig.yaml:
    options:
      "@massivescale/tsp-aspnetcore-api":
        templates:
          bool-string-converter: "./templates/bool-string-converter.hbs"

  ── Template variables ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  (none — this template renders a fully static class body)

  ── Example customisations ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

  • Emit "True"/"False" (capitalised) instead of lowercase:
      writer.WriteStringValue(value ? "True" : "False");

  • Make the class internal for single-assembly projects:
      internal sealed class BooleanStringJsonConverter : JsonConverter<bool>
